      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (viscosity, density, boundary conditions) must have documented uncertainty bounds derived from measurement data.",
      "rationale": "Blood analogue viscosity and density were characterized with ±1.5% and ±0.3% uncertainty respectively. Inlet flow rate and outlet pressure boundary conditions carry documented measurement uncertainties propagated through a Monte Carlo UQ analysis (500 samples). The UQ results confirm that output NIH uncertainty is within acceptable bounds; a planned follow-on sensitivity analysis will identify which of the five uncertain inputs contributes most to output variance, but this has not yet been completed."
    },
